narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it if you are working in a lab and want to get to know the background of the work you are doing. It really helps you understand things better.
Directed research can be great. Do it with something that interests you.
I would recommend it, as long as you are familiar with the lab and lab instructors.
If you're into research, take this class.

Psychology 495 is a good way to get hands on experience with research. You get to participate in the planning and execution of a study. You are also able to create a close relationship with your adviser if you choose, which is great if you need a mentor. Take this course if you are going to psych grad school or if you are just interested in research.
